                    <li><strong class="font-semibold">Privacy & Security:</strong> Traditional software download and server-side web platforms risk exposing your documents. PageSlice processes all files inside your web browser using HTML5 features—your files never leave your device.</li>
                    <li><strong class="font-semibold">Speed & Accessibility:</strong> No installation, sign-ups, or subscriptions. It runs on Mac, Windows, iOS, and Android, making it the <strong class="font-semibold">best free pdf extractor tool 2025 2026</strong> for zero-friction workflows.</li>
                    <li><strong class="font-semibold">Multi-Format Versatility:</strong> Most basic software only splits PDFs. PageSlice merges, deletes pages, and converts Word docs, PowerPoints, and images simultaneously.</li>
                  </ol>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <footer class="border-t border-neutral-800/50 mt-8 pt-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-6 text-[11px]">
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary uppercase font-mono mb-1">How to Convert Photo to PDF on iPhone</h4>
                <p class="font-inter leading-relaxed">Open PageSlice in Safari or Chrome, tap "Browse Files", select images from the gallery, arrange the order, and click "Extract".</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary uppercase font-mono mb-1">How to Convert Word Document to PDF</h4>
                <p class="font-inter leading-relaxed">Select your DOCX file, wait for local conversion to finish in your browser memory, and download the compiled file.</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-bold text-primary uppercase font-mono mb-1">How to Delete PDF Pages</h4>
                <p class="font-inter leading-relaxed">Drag your PDF, select only the pages you want to keep (effectively deleting the unselected ones), and click the extract button.</p>
