                <p class="text-mute font-inter leading-relaxed">There are no page extraction limits. Since PageSlice works entirely client-side using your browser memory, you can extract as many pages as your computer or device can process.</p>
              </div>

              <div class="border-b border-neutral-800/50 pb-6 text-left">
                <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-white uppercase tracking-wide mb-2"><span class="text-primary font-bold">Q /</span> Is it possible to extract pages from a PDF and save them as a new file?</h3>
                <p class="text-mute font-inter leading-relaxed">Yes. When you click "Extract Selected Pages", PageSlice generates a new, separate PDF file in your browser memory and triggers an automatic download, saving the extracted pages as a new file.</p>
